VOIP Directory — MySQL Fix Instructions
========================================

PROBLEM: Node.js hangs when connecting to MySQL 8.0 over TCP.
CAUSE:   MySQL 8.0 root user uses caching_sha2_password which requires SSL.
         mysql2 connects without SSL and stalls.

─────────────────────────────────────────
STEP 1 — Run in MySQL Workbench
─────────────────────────────────────────

-- Check current auth plugin for root:
SELECT user, host, plugin FROM mysql.user WHERE user = 'root';

-- Create a dedicated app user with the simpler auth plugin:
CREATE USER IF NOT EXISTS 'voipapp'@'localhost'
    IDENTIFIED WITH mysql_native_password BY 'Cityvoip@502';

GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON bcc_voip_directory.* TO 'voipapp'@'localhost';

FLUSH PRIVILEGES;


─────────────────────────────────────────
STEP 2 — Update .env on the server (PowerShell as Admin)
─────────────────────────────────────────

@"
DB_HOST=127.0.0.1
DB_USER=voipapp
DB_PASSWORD=Cityvoip@502
DB_NAME=bcc_voip_directory
PORT=5001
"@ | Out-File -FilePath "C:\inetpub\wwwroot\VOIP-Directory\backend\.env" -Encoding utf8


─────────────────────────────────────────
STEP 3 — Test the connection (PowerShell)
─────────────────────────────────────────

cd C:\inetpub\wwwroot\VOIP-Directory\backend

node -e "const m=require('mysql2'); const c=m.createConnection({host:'127.0.0.1',user:'voipapp',password:'Cityvoip@502',database:'bcc_voip_directory',connectTimeout:5000}); c.connect(e=>{console.log(e?'FAILED: '+e.message:'CONNECTED OK'); c.end(); process.exit(0);});"

Expected output: CONNECTED OK


─────────────────────────────────────────
STEP 4 — Restart PM2
─────────────────────────────────────────

pm2 restart bcc-directory-backend


─────────────────────────────────────────
STEP 5 — Run full diagnostics
─────────────────────────────────────────

node diagnose.js

All items should show [OK]. Then try logging in at http://9.135.112.20


─────────────────────────────────────────
STEP 6 — If CONNECTED OK but app still fails
─────────────────────────────────────────

Check PM2 logs for new errors:

pm2 logs bcc-directory-backend --lines 30 --nostream
